---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Aetna International in Thailand', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-compliance', text: 'Thai Visa Compliance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'thailand-network', text: 'Network Coverage in Thailand', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'us-coverage', text: 'US Coverage Advantage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'vs-local-options', text: 'vs Thai Insurers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-its-for', text: 'Who Should Choose Aetna', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Thailand', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance' },
  { title: 'Aetna International Review', href: '/providers/aetna-international' },
  { title: 'Aetna vs GeoBlue', href: '/compare/aetna-international-vs-geoblue' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'thailandPrice', header: 'Thailand (Age 50)' },
  { key: 'usIncluded', header: 'US Coverage' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Pioneer', coverage: 'Inpatient + Emergency', thailandPrice: '$150-200/mo', usIncluded: 'Full integrated' },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Prime', coverage: 'Inpatient + Outpatient', thailandPrice: '$200-280/mo', usIncluded: 'Full integrated' },
  { plan: 'Pioneer Platinum', coverage: 'Comprehensive', thailandPrice: '$280-380/mo', usIncluded: 'Full integrated' },
];

const comparisonColumns = [
  { key: 'factor', header: 'Factor' },
  { key: 'aetna', header: 'Aetna International' },
  { key: 'thai', header: 'Thai Insurers' },
];

const comparisonRows = [
  { factor: 'Monthly Cost (Age 50)', aetna: '$200-280', thai: '$60-150' },
  { factor: 'US Coverage', aetna: 'Full Aetna network', thai: 'Not available' },
  { factor: 'Network in Thailand', aetna: 'Good', thai: 'Excellent' },
  { factor: 'TGIA Approved', aetna: 'Verify', thai: 'Yes (most)' },
  { factor: 'Annual Maximum', aetna: '$1-2M', thai: 'Varies (often lower)' },
  { factor: 'Portability', aetna: 'Worldwide', thai: 'Thailand only' },
  { factor: 'Best For', aetna: 'US expats', thai: 'Long-term Thailand residents' },
];

const hospitalColumns = [
  { key: 'city', header: 'City' },
  { key: 'hospitals', header: 'Network Hospitals' },
  { key: 'directBilling', header: 'Direct Billing' },
];

const hospitalRows = [
  { city: 'Bangkok', hospitals: 'Bumrungrad International, Bangkok Hospital, BNH Hospital', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Chiang Mai', hospitals: 'Bangkok Hospital Chiang Mai, Chiang Mai Ram Hospital', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Phuket', hospitals: 'Bangkok Hospital Phuket, Phuket International Hospital', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Pattaya', hospitals: 'Bangkok Hospital Pattaya, Pattaya International Hospital', directBilling: true },
  { city: 'Hua Hin', hospitals: 'Bangkok Hospital Hua Hin', directBilling: true },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Aetna International Health Insurance in Thailand"
  description="Guide to using Aetna International in Thailand. Best for US expats needing US network access. Visa compliance, Thai network, and pricing details."
  headline="Aetna International Health Insurance in Thailand"
  subheadline="Full US network access built in. The smart choice for American expats in Thailand who visit family or might need US specialists."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/thailand-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get an Aetna Thailand Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/aetna-international"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Aetna International in Thailand</h2>
  <p>
    Thailand attracts many American retirees with its low cost of living, excellent healthcare, and tropical climate. For US expats, Aetna International offers a key advantage: integrated US coverage. When you visit family in the States or need a US specialist, your Aetna plan works seamlessly.
  </p>
  <p>
    Most Thailand expats don't need US coverage—they're here full-time and Thai healthcare is excellent. But for Americans who maintain US ties, Aetna provides something local Thai insurers can't: a single policy that works in both countries.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">1.7M+</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Providers (US + intl)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Full</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">US network included</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">24/7</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">English support</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get a Thailand-Specific Quote"
    description="See what Aetna International costs for US expats in Thailand."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="visa-compliance">Thai Visa Compliance</h2>
  <p>
    Thailand has strict insurance requirements for O-A, O-X, and LTR visas. Aetna International may meet these requirements, but TGIA approval is essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Important: Verify TGIA Approval</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800">
      Aetna International is a US-based insurer, and its TGIA approval status may vary. <strong>Always verify at longstay.tgia.org</strong> before relying on Aetna for visa applications. If Aetna isn't currently approved, consider using a TGIA-approved Thai insurer (Pacific Cross, AXA Thailand) for your visa, then switch to or add Aetna afterward.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3>O-A Visa (1-Year Retirement)</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>400,000 THB (~$11,500) inpatient + 40,000 THB (~$1,150) outpatient, OR</li>
    <li>$100,000 USD / 3,000,000 THB total medical coverage</li>
    <li>Must be from a TGIA-approved insurer</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Aetna Pioneer Prime and Platinum plans exceed these coverage minimums if approved.
  </p>

  <h3>O-X Visa (10-Year Retirement)</h3>
  <p>
    Same requirements as O-A. Verify TGIA approval before applying.
  </p>

  <h3>LTR Visa (Long-Term Resident)</h3>
  <p>
    Requires $50,000 USD minimum coverage. Aetna plans exceed this with $1-2M limits. LTR visa acceptance of international insurers may be more flexible than O-A/O-X.
  </p>

  <h3>Non-O Visa (No Requirement)</h3>
  <p>
    If you're extending a Non-O visa based on retirement or Thai spouse, health insurance is not mandatory. Aetna is a strong choice for comprehensive coverage without visa constraints.
  </p>

  <h2 id="thailand-network">Network Coverage in Thailand</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna has a good network in Thailand, covering major private hospitals in Bangkok and expat destinations.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={hospitalColumns} rows={hospitalRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Coverage by Region</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bangkok:</strong> Good coverage at top hospitals including Bumrungrad International</li>
    <li><strong>Chiang Mai:</strong> Network hospitals serving the large expat community</li>
    <li><strong>Beach destinations:</strong> Coverage in Phuket, Pattaya, Hua Hin</li>
    <li><strong>Smaller cities:</strong> May need to travel or use reimbursement</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Thailand's Healthcare Quality</h3>
  <p>
    Thailand has 62+ JCI-accredited hospitals—more than any other Southeast Asian country. Bumrungrad International in Bangkok is one of the world's premier medical tourism destinations. You're getting excellent care regardless of insurer.
  </p>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    Aetna Pioneer plans include US coverage—no add-on needed.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <em>Prices include worldwide coverage with full US access. Age 50 shown (common for Thailand expats).</em>
  </p>

  <h3>Plan Recommendations for Thailand</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pioneer:</strong> Hospital-only. Good for healthy expats who pay routine care out of pocket—affordable in Thailand.</li>
    <li><strong>Pioneer Prime:</strong> The practical choice. Includes outpatient, meets typical visa requirements if TGIA-approved.</li>
    <li><strong>Pioneer Platinum:</strong> Comprehensive coverage. Best for families or those with ongoing health needs.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Navigator Plans (Modular Option)</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna's Navigator plans let you customize coverage:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Core hospital coverage (required)</li>
    <li>Optional outpatient module</li>
    <li>Optional dental and vision</li>
    <li>Optional maternity</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Navigator can reduce costs if you only need hospital coverage and want to pay routine care out of pocket.
  </p>

  <h3>Deductible Strategy</h3>
  <p>
    Thai healthcare is affordable:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Doctor visit: $30-80</li>
    <li>Specialist: $50-150</li>
    <li>Lab work: $20-60</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    A higher deductible ($2,000-5,000) significantly reduces premiums. Pay routine care out of pocket and use insurance for hospitals.
  </p>

  <h2 id="us-coverage">US Coverage Advantage</h2>
  <p>
    The main reason to choose Aetna over Thai insurers:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">US Network Benefits</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-blue-800">
        <li>Full Aetna US network access</li>
        <li>Direct billing at US hospitals</li>
        <li>Aetna's negotiated US rates</li>
        <li>No separate add-on cost</li>
        <li>Coverage continuity if you return</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Why It Matters</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Visit family in the US? Covered.</li>
        <li>US specialist needed? Direct access.</li>
        <li>Moving back? No coverage gap.</li>
        <li>Medicare doesn't work abroad.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Medicare Replacement</h3>
  <p>
    US Medicare doesn't cover you in Thailand. For American retirees, Aetna effectively replaces Medicare abroad while keeping US coverage active for visits home.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Built-In US Coverage"
    description="No surprise premiums when visiting family or needing US care."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/aetna-international"
  />

  <h2 id="vs-local-options">vs Thai Insurers</h2>
  <p>
    How does Aetna compare to Thai insurers like Pacific Cross or AXA Thailand?
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={comparisonColumns} rows={comparisonRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Key Differences</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>US coverage:</strong> Thai insurers don't cover the US. If you visit America at all, you'd need separate travel insurance. Aetna covers both countries seamlessly.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>TGIA approval:</strong> Thai insurers are reliably TGIA-approved for visas. Aetna's status may vary—verify before relying on it for visa applications.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Price:</strong> Thai insurers cost 30-50% less than Aetna. If you don't need US coverage, local options are better value.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-its-for">Who Should Choose Aetna</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Ideal For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
        <li>US citizens in Thailand</li>
        <li>Those who visit the US regularly</li>
        <li>People with US doctors or specialists</li>
        <li>Expats who might repatriate</li>
        <li>Those wanting Medicare replacement</li>
        <li>Non-O visa holders (no TGIA needed)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>O-A/O-X applicants (TGIA approval uncertain)</li>
        <li>Non-US expats (no US benefit)</li>
        <li>Budget-focused (Thai insurers cheaper)</li>
        <li>Those who never visit the US</li>
        <li>Age 75+ (limited acceptance)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is Aetna TGIA-approved for Thai O-A visas?</h3>
  <p>
    TGIA approval status varies for international insurers. <strong>Always verify at longstay.tgia.org</strong> before your visa application. If uncertain, use a Thai insurer for the visa and add Aetna afterward if needed.
  </p>

  <h3>Does Aetna replace Medicare in Thailand?</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna provides coverage abroad that Medicare doesn't offer. For US retirees in Thailand, it effectively serves as Medicare replacement for Thai care and provides US coverage for visits home.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I get Aetna at age 70+?</h3>
  <p>
    Aetna accepts new applicants up to age 74. If you're older, consider Pacific Cross which accepts up to age 80.
  </p>

  <h3>Should I use Aetna or a Thai insurer?</h3>
  <p>
    If you need US coverage, choose Aetna. If you're staying in Thailand full-time without US ties, Thai insurers offer better value and guaranteed TGIA approval.
  </p>

  <h3>What about Aetna Thailand (Allianz Ayudhya)?</h3>
  <p>
    "Aetna Thailand" was acquired by Allianz Ayudhya in 2022. Aetna International is the global expat product—different from the former local Thai brand.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready for Coverage in Thailand?"
    description="Get a personalized Aetna International quote."
    buttonText="Get Your Quote"
    buttonHref="/go/aetna-international"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. TGIA approval status and visa requirements change. Always verify at longstay.tgia.org before visa applications. We are not insurance brokers or immigration consultants.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
